<topic id="code-templates">
  <title>Code Templates</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Editing XML Documents<indexterm>streamline with content completion<indexterm>code
              templates</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>You can define short names for predefined blocks of code called <term>code templates</term>.
      The short names are displayed in the Content Completion window when the word at cursor
      position is a prefix of such a short name. If there is no prefix at cursor position (a
      whitespace precedes the cursor), all the code templates are listed.</p>
    <p><ph keyref="product"/> comes with numerous predefined code templates. You can also <xref
        href="../topics/preferences-editor-code-templates.dita">define</xref> your own code
      templates for any type of editor. <ph
        product="editor editorEclipse developer developerEclipse">For more details, see the <xref
          href="../topics/xslt-code-templates.dita">example for XSLT editor code
        templates.</xref></ph></p>
    <p>To obtain the template list, you use the <uicontrol
        conref="oxygen-shortcuts-list.dita#oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_space"/> content completion
      shortcut key, or the <uicontrol
        conref="oxygen-shortcuts-list.dita#oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_shift_space"/> code templates
      shortcut key. The first shortcut displays the code templates in the same <xref
        href="../topics/streamline-with-content-completion.dita">content completion list with
        elements from the schema of the document</xref>. The second shortcut displays only the code
      templates and is the default shortcut of the action <menucascade>
        <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Content Completion</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Show Code Templates</uicontrol>
      </menucascade>.</p>
    <p>The syntax of the code templates allows you to use the following <term>editor
        variables</term>:<ul>
        <li conref="../topics/editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edVar-caret"/>
        <li conref="../topics/editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edvar-selection"/>
        <li conref="../topics/editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edVar-ask"/>
        <li conref="../topics/editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edvar-timestamp"/>
        <li conref="../topics/editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edvar-uuid"/>
        <li conref="../topics/editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edVar-id"/>
        <li conref="../topics/editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edVar-cfn"/>
        <li conref="../topics/editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edVar-cfne"/>
        <li conref="../topics/editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edvar-cf"/>
        <li conref="../topics/editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edVar-cfd"/>
        <li conref="../topics/editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edVar-frameworksDir"/>
        <li conref="../topics/editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edVar-pd"/>
        <li conref="../topics/editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edVar-oxygenInstallDir"/>
        <li conref="../topics/editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edVar-homeDir"/>
        <li conref="../topics/editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edVar-pn"/>
        <li conref="../topics/editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edvar-env"/>
        <li conref="../topics/editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edVar-system"/>
        <li conref="../topics/editor-variables.dita#editor-variables/edVar-date"/>
      </ul></p>
    <p>To watch our video demonstration about code templates, go to <xref
        href="http://oxygenxml.com/demo/Code_Templates.html" format="html" scope="external"
        >http://oxygenxml.com/demo/Code_Templates.html</xref>.</p>
